---
// About — approved bio (May 2026)
---

<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">About</p>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          I'm Rose &mdash; a vMix operator, graphics integrator, and engineer in charge
          based in New York City. Since 2019 I've been running desks at esports tournaments,
          corporate roadshows, satellite media tours, concerts, and live broadcasts, making
          sure the show goes out clean and on time.
        </p>
        <p>
          I got into production sideways. Digital Humanities degree from RIT, a League of
          Legends casting gig in college, and a lot of hours during the COVID lockdown teaching
          myself vMix from the ground up. What started as necessity turned into a career I've
          built deliberately. My edge is on the technical side &mdash; custom graphics integration,
          XML and API-driven data sources, VB.NET scripting for vMix automation, and building
          the kind of dashboards that let a small crew punch above their weight.
        </p>
        <p>
          I operate through Rose Media Group and work locally in New York and regionally to
          DC and Boston. For esports productions, I'm also available remote &mdash; running a
          dedicated studio set up for multi-caller shows at 1080p60 with records.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're looking for someone who can own the desk, own the technical decisions,
          and keep the show moving &mdash; let's talk.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="about-aside">
        <img src="/images/rose_about.jpg" alt="Rose, Rose Media Group" class="about-photo" />

        <div class="about-quick">
          <div class="quick-item">
            <span class="quick-label">Based</span>
            <span>New York City</span>
          </div>
          <div class="quick-item">
            <span class="quick-label">LLC</span>
            <span>Rose Media Group</span>
          </div>
          <div class="quick-item">
            <span class="quick-label">Since</span>
            <span>2019</span>
          </div>
          <div class="quick-item">
            <span class="quick-label">Coverage</span>
            <span>NYC · DC · Boston · Remote (esports)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="quick-item">
            <span class="quick-label">Status</span>
            <span>Available &mdash; email or text to book</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .about-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-aside {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: 80px;
  }

  .about-photo {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: block;
  }

  .about-quick {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .quick-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .quick-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-alt);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .about-aside { position: static; }
  }
</style>
